Download and Install XAMPP:

Download XAMPP from https://www.apachefriends.org/index.html.
Install XAMPP on your machine by following the installation instructions for your operating system.
Clone or Download Project:

Clone your project repository or download the project files from the repository.
Move Project to htdocs:

Locate the XAMPP htdocs directory on your machine.
On Windows: C:\xampp\htdocs\Web - Event Manager
On Linux: /opt/lampp/htdocs/Web - Event Manager
Move the entire project folder into the htdocs directory.
Import Database:

Find the eventorganizer.sql file in your project folder.
Open phpMyAdmin by going to http://localhost/phpmyadmin in your web browser.
Create a new database named eventorganizer.
Select the newly created database and go to the "Import" tab.
Upload the eventorganizer.sql file and execute the import to populate the database with the necessary tables and data.
Start XAMPP:

Launch XAMPP and ensure both Apache and MySQL services are running.
Open Your Web Browser:

Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost/Web - Event Manager.
Done:

Your project should now be running locally. Explore it in your web browser.